metadata.description: Although he was a wandering warrior during his lifetime, his strength cannot be underestimated. He brings a famous blade Muramasa, which contains a strong evil breath. After resurrection, He is still wandering, In pursuit of comprehending the strongest Bushido as the ultimate goal!

metadata.description: Its soul has been manipulated by the devil. It's intimate with Deviruchies and did many bad things. In the depths of its fallen heart, it's always looking for the answer to a question - what is the bottom line?
A well-known goat-headed demon who uses a giant reaper scythe. Like Demon King Morroc, he has a strong desire to destroy and kill. And wherever he goes is full of death...
One of the leaders of Glast Heim and the absolute master of dark magic and a symbol of fear and despair. After being locked by him, You will fall into the endless darkness!

card_data.name: Dark Lord Card
card_data.effect: When suffering attack from physical skills, Caster has a chance to trigger Meteor Storm Lv.10

metadata.description: Its holiness, Goodness and integrity are deeply rooted in people's heart. Its existence is to protect the world from being invaded by devils. As an Angel, it has extremely high stats and attack, and is a loyal protector of human beings.

Looks like a gentleman who is gentle, Intelligent and attractive to females. He is cursed, Immortal and bloodthirsty. His inner quality is weird, his behavior is absurd and his ambition is huge but distorted. His desire to conquer is strong and the means he chooses are crazy.

card_data.name: Dracula Card
card_data.effect: Any attack has a 10% chance to proportionally convert the damage caused by enemy into your own SP value.

metadata.description: Senior Bathories who were Black Witches and driven away by the Mages in the land because of their study of banned spells. They were cursed and turned into monsters. They ride broomsticks in the Clock Tower Labyrinth and are a nightmare for many children of Al De Baran.

It is said that the three alchemists who created the Clock Tower Labyrinth were persecuted by the Senate. Eventually the Senate members' souls were trapped by the revenging alchemists, Made into clocks, and always lingering in the labyrinth.

Black witches who have been driven away because their study of the prohibited spells. They were cursed and became monsters. They were riding the broomsticks in the Clock Tower Labyrinth and they were the nightmare of many citizens of Al De Baran in their childhood.
A Fantasy Elder tribe that has existed before the Ragnarok times. They were cursed by the gods and demons for acquiring a forbidden magic. From then on, they live between life and death.

metadata.description: For some reason, in the book "Midgard Monsters" compiled by the famous adventurer Ms. Letin, this dangerous creature swimming in cave waters were marked as "women’s public enemy".
A rare cave creature of Stainers. It's a scavenger, but occasionally it will actively attack. The rounded shell protects its soft wings.
A self-disciplined alchemy creature. The original purpose of making it is unknown. It would attack any intruder in the labyrinth in the Clock Tower Labyrinth.
A sub-species of Wormtails. They were contaminated by the frenzied magic power during the battle of gods. Their body organization has mutated in the process of evolution. Don't underestimate them.
